I believe that, if it hasn't already been done, it's important for you to know that you will always encounter people who may not necessarily agree with your choices, who may not like your style, your gestures, or whatever else... but never stop believing in yourself, stay as you are, with your personality and sensitivity that won the jury's favor; Another thing, not everyone is given the courage to do so! This will allow you to move forward, and one can only observe that you fit in with any repertoire, I even find that sometimes your versions are better than the original! You seem humble and deeply kind, you have talent and generosity, you were not one of those on whom I would have bet at the outset, and honestly, I do not remember not appreciating any of your performances, I find you amazing... to finish, I really enjoyed your interpretation of Gainsbourg, I had also liked the original but for once I clearly heard the lyrics, we perhaps had a little the impression that you were careful not to make any gestures, you transmitted emotion to me through my television so I do not understand why 3 members of the jury did not feel it! So, I wish you all the best, keep your feet on the ground, do not change what you are, stay humble, stay yourself, make good use of constructive criticism and do not pay attention to those that are not.
